{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/control-your-keyboard-using-python/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Kevin Ponce Blog","author":"Kevin Ponce"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"8a10e236-6303-5ae7-a959-8e68d926d930","excerpt":"Here is a simple snippet of code that allows you open notes, create a new note, and type a message programmatically. It also prints out all of the keyboard keysâ€¦","html":"<p>Here is a simple snippet of code that allows you open notes, create a new note, and type a message programmatically.</p>\n<p>It also prints out all of the keyboard keys to use with hotkey.</p>\n<p>Before you can use it, make sure you install pyautogui.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">$ pip install pyautogui</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token comment\"># pip install pyautogui</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> pyautogui\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> time\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pyautogui<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>KEYBOARD_KEYS<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\npyautogui<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hotkey<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'command'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">' '</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\npyautogui<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>typewrite<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'notes'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\npyautogui<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hotkey<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'enter'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\ntime<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>sleep<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\npyautogui<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>hotkey<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'command'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'n'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\npyautogui<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>typewrite<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'I see you'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Voila.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Control your keyboard using python","date":"December 26, 2019","description":"How to control your keyboard using pythong.","author":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/control-your-keyboard-using-python/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/arduino-arcade-button/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Arduino Arcade Button","tags":["arduino","circuit"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/control-your-mouse-using-python/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Control your mouse using python","tags":["python"]}}}}}